Responses.NAM1 - Response Text: Thanks for trusting me, outlander.
You murdered Nine-Toes. I'm not fond of your kind, but the murderer was a Dunmer, not an Argonian.
You murdered Nine-Toes. I'm not fond of Argonians, but he was not the real murderer.
You brought justice to his murderer. I am grateful.
You should speak with Nileno Dorvayn at the Hlaalu Council Hall.
I believe she is offering a reward.
I heard you found the real murderer. It is good to trust each other among these slavers, outlander.
I heard you found the real murderer. I am grateful to you, soft-skin.
You solved the murder of Ralen Hlaalo.
I believe that Thanelen Velas was the murderer.
If so, you have already taken care of the matter. My thanks from House Hlaalu.
You killed both the suspects...
While murder is usually bad business, I cannot fault your actions here.
Take these 1000 drakes as thanks from House Hlaalu.
You killed Nine-Toes. House Hlaalu will not soon forget this act of vengeance.

Why not ask Ralen Hlaalo's servant, Uryne Nirith. She's probably still in Hlaalo Manor.
I don't think she has anywhere else to go.
I heard that a red-haired Dunmer was seen leaving Hlaalo Manor the day that Ralen Hlaalo was murdered.
I have heard only false rumors. Nine-Toes cannot be the murderer.
I heard that Nine-Toes the Argonian killed him.

Me? No, you are mistaken. It was that Argonian, Nine-Toes.
Yes, I was one of Ralen Hlaalo's servants. I saw the Dunmer who killed him with my own eyes. I can give you the murderer's description.
I have heard the rumors, but I am not a murderer. I believe someone is spreading these rumors because I am a foreigner and an Argonian.
You've been expelled from House Hlaalu. You must make amends.
Ralen Hlaalo was a noble who lived here in Balmora.
When you find out who murdered Ralen Hlaalo, kill them so that no one will ever dare raise their hand against a Hlaalu noble again.
Here is a key to Hlaalo Manor where Ser Ralen was killed.
